---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Peace Officer Standards And Training | PoliceConduct.org"
  pagePath="/partner/peace-officer-standards-and-training/"
>
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">POST</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">The POST Modernization Initiative</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Partnering with policeconduct.org to transform compliance,
              training, and public trust.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  State POST Directors and Executive Commissioners
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  2026 mandates demand modern reporting without doubling staff.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">1. The problem: the compliance gap</h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              By 2026, new state laws have fundamentally changed the reporting
              burden for POST organizations.
            </p>
            <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The mandate crisis
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  States like Texas and New York now require reporting of all
                  misconduct investigations, even those not sustained, within 30
                  days. Most POSTs are still using manual forms or fragmented
                  legacy portals.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The visibility gap
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  The National Decertification Index only acts as a pointer. It
                  does not show the patterns of behavior that precede a crisis.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The training vacuum
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Curriculum updates are reactive. POSTs lack a feedback loop to
                  prove that a 40-hour De-escalation course reduced use-of-force
                  incidents in the field.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  What we hear in 2026
                </div>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Data</span>
                    <span>Mandates expand faster than staff capacity.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Risk</span>
                    <span>Wandering officers create costly liability.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Trust</span>
                    <span
                      >Public wants transparency without compromising privacy.</span
                    >
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Our solution: the source of truth platform
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          policeconduct.org is a unified data ecosystem that serves as the
          operating system for statewide standards.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  A. Automated reporting workflow
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">The SB 2 / MIR solution</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    One-click reporting for misconduct, fitness-for-duty, and
                    separations.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Automated dashboard that flags serious misconduct for
                    immediate investigator review.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  B. The conduct passport
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">
                  Close the wandering officer loophole
                </h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Track administrative integrity, not just criminal
                    convictions.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Hiring chiefs see sustained findings, dishonest
                    resignations, and training certifications.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  C. Evidence-informed training
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">The 30-60-90 day feedback loop</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Correlate training modules with outcomes like complaint
                    reductions.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Convert community sentiment into priority topics for the
                    next curriculum cycle.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-secondary rounded-0 border-dark mt-4 mb-0">
          Example: Officers who took the 2025 Procedural Justice course saw a
          14% drop in disrespect complaints compared to the control group.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">3. Strategic outcomes for 2026</h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Priority</th>
                <th scope="col">POST challenge</th>
                <th scope="col">policeconduct.org value</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Legal compliance</strong></td>
                <td>Overwhelmed by new 10-30 day reporting laws.</td>
                <td><strong>Automated</strong> data ingestion and flagging.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Risk management</strong></td>
                <td>Millions in state liability for wandering officers.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Proactive</strong> flagging of at-risk hires via Conduct
                  Passports.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Budget defense</strong></td>
                <td>Hard to prove evidence-based training ROI.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Real-time</strong> correlation between training and conduct
                  data.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Public trust</strong></td>
                <td>Perception of a black box process.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Public-facing</strong> transparency dashboards (anonymized/aggregated).</td
                >
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">
              4. Why partner with policeconduct.org?
            </h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-2">
              We are not just a software vendor; we are a data partner.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>
                <strong>Interoperability:</strong> We sit on top of existing systems.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Security:</strong> 2026 CJIS-compliant cloud architecture
                and audit logs.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Scalability:</strong> From 50-officer departments to 50,000-officer
                mandates.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Suggested next step
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Want a technical use case for a specific state (California,
                  Texas, or Florida) that maps 2025-2026 reporting forms into a
                  digital dashboard?
                </p>
                <a
                  class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
                  href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20a%20POST%20Modernization%20Initiative%20use%20case%20for%20my%20state."
                >
                  Request a tailored use case
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
